{"TopicId":181827,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"How to rescale Kerbin in 1.6.1.2401","CreatedByName":"AeroGav","CreatedById":152027,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-30T17:03:10Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"AeroGav","CreatedById":152027,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-30T17:03:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve spent the past four hours downloading stuff haphazardly and restarting KSP,\u00A0 \u00A0trying to get a real scale Kerbin system for a challenge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAccording to this post,\u00A0 I need Sigma Dimensions and Kopernicus, but nothing seems to happen when I copy into Gamedata folder\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3866372677\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/181801-ssto-help/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=3531504\u0026amp;embedComment=3531504\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:291px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nam using v.0.10.1 of sigma (latest)\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Sigma88/Sigma-Dimensions/releases/tag/v.0.10.1\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Sigma88/Sigma-Dimensions/releases/tag/v.0.10.1\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand 1.3.1-7 of Kopernic\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Kopernicus/Kopernicus/releases/tag/release-1.3.1-7\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Kopernicus/Kopernicus/releases/tag/release-1.3.1-7\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen this failed, I deleted all my mods,\u00A0 and started over, manually installing\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/KSP-RO/RealSolarSystem/releases/tag/v14.0.0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/KSP-\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Realism Overhaul (mod)\u0022\u003ERO\u003C/abbr\u003E/RealSolarSystem/releases/tag/v14.0.0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand its dependencies (incl. Sigma).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll this appears to do is add extra runways to a stock Kerbin.\u00A0 Orbital velocities etc. are unchanged.\u00A0 However,\u00A0 the first post on the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E thread indicates that installing\u00A0 a fresh copy of KSP 1.4.5 is the first step,\u00A0 so either i have to roll back to a much older ksp, or the thread\u0027s just not been updated in a while and that was the latest at time of writing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/91917-kerikbalm/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002291917\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/91917-kerikbalm/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@KerikBalm\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0was able to get his working however on 1.6, if i\u0027m interpreting his post correctly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"adsii1970","CreatedById":89014,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-30T17:20:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoved from Add-On Releases to Add-On Discussions since this is more of a procedural question about using a mod (Add-On). The Add-On Releases section is supposed to be for threads that are actual releases of Add-Ons. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-30T17:45:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223531604\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548867790\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152027\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AeroGav\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, AeroGav said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003Eand 1.3.1-7 of Kopernic\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Kopernicus/Kopernicus/releases/tag/release-1.3.1-7\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Kopernicus/Kopernicus/releases/tag/release-1.3.1-7\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is the problem. Kopernicus is version locked, therefore you have to use version \u003Cb\u003E1.6.1\u003C/b\u003E-1 when using KSP \u003Cb\u003E1.6.1\u003C/b\u003E.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-30T17:53:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Kopernicus/Kopernicus/releases/latest\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Kopernicus/Kopernicus/releases/latest\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3603939500\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/181547-161-1-backports-kopernicus-kittopiatech/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:227px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYea, seems like you got an old version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI updated kopernicus, not sigma dimensions, and it worked. Kopernicus definitely needs to be up to date.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AeroGav","CreatedById":152027,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-30T18:12:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMagnifico,\u00A0 Galileo.\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 I just went to the tracking station and Mun is 34 million KM away..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOMG\u00A0 it\u0027s huge\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022f7676ab59158d78480b19c29c527c851--drama-\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022232\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.pinimg.com/236x/f7/67/6a/f7676ab59158d78480b19c29c527c851--drama-queens-scream-queens.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022230\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-30T20:44:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReal Solar System works fine in 1.4 and on. However it does not use Sigma Dimensions because it is already real size\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-31T09:09:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223531758\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548881088\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150244\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nightside\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Nightside said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReal Solar System works fine in 1.4 and on. However it does not use Sigma Dimensions because it is already real size\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYea.. sigma dimensions is just for rescalingthe stock system, but keeping it fictional. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E gives you the real size with real planets.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat said... it seems he\u0027s just interested in the challenges of SSTOing on a bigger planet (this started from a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E help thread, in which I was sharing designs for cargo SSTOs for a 3x kerbin, that work with huge margins on stock Kerbin)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223531646\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181827\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221548871966\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152027\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AeroGav\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, AeroGav said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMagnifico,\u00A0 Galileo.\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 I just went to the tracking station and Mun is 34 million KM away..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOMG\u00A0 it\u0027s huge\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022f7676ab59158d78480b19c29c527c851--drama-\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022232\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.pinimg.com/236x/f7/67/6a/f7676ab59158d78480b19c29c527c851--drama-queens-scream-queens.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022230\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut.... the real moon is only 360 thousand to 405 thousand kM away...a factor of 10 increase and its 3.4 million... did you somehow scale up \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E by 100 fold using \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E and sigma dimensions???\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}